**Investigated**: Comprehensive code review of host migration implementation spanning 12 files with 366 insertions. Examined core migrateHost helper function with deterministic counterclockwise seat selection, integration points across four server handlers (join-handler grace-expiry trigger, leave-handler intentional departure triggers, turn-timer auto-end, and hostless room recovery), client-side phase-conditional toast rendering in GameTable.vue and RoomView.vue, and complete test coverage including unit tests and integration tests for all 18 transition scenarios. Validated all 17 acceptance criteria against implementation with focus on order-of-operations invariants (capture wasHost before releaseSeat, run migration after seat release but before final broadcasts) and regression compatibility with Stories 4B.3 pause mechanics and 4B.5 departure flows.

**Learned**: Host migration implementation follows critical pattern: capture host state before mutation (wasHost flag before releaseSeat) because seat release removes player from room.players map. Migration triggers at exactly four points where host role becomes invalid: grace-expiry timeout after 30s disconnect, lobby/scoreboard LEAVE_ROOM, departure vote dead_seat outcome, and auto-end game on departure. Hostless room recovery promotes first reconnecting player when no one has isHost flag, preventing permanent host loss. Client implementation diverged from spec by placing toast watchers directly in UI components rather than useRoomConnection composable, following existing 4B.5 toast pattern. All migration broadcasts occur before final state broadcasts to ensure event-then-snapshot ordering for clients. Story closes T12 and T13 gaps from Story 4B.5 where host could be dead-seated or leave lobby without reassignment.

